				<td colspan="2"><span>Bards aren't dead. This is a halfassed implementation that will always be surpassed by someone manually twisting. The melody bards will be easy to spot, while the old skilled bards will still continue to be their awesome selves.
<br />

<br />
There are a few ways to make melody work very well, but it will take nearly the same amount of attention as manually twisting anyways. The sky is not falling, very few melody bards will go anywhere.
<br />

<br />
Besides, if people wanted to autotwist, there a much better (albeit illegitimate) ways of doing it than this. This is just a gesture to bards saying:
<br />

<br />
 &quot;We don't hate you, see? Sure, we took away your area kiting, but look! A /melody command! We love you too.&quot;
<br />

<br />
I repeat, the sky is not falling. Good bards will play with this for a while, then most likely discard it (like I have already.) The bad bards will embrace it and continue to be bad bards. This whole thing changes nearly nothing.
<br />

