				<td colspan="2"><span>I dont understand the hate for /melody . Right here on this forum are threads about how to twist with hot keys . /melody does make it easier to twist in one way, but most bards wont use it ( i dont ). I either manually twist or use hot keys when my wrist starts to hurt.
<br />

<br />
If i recall , at least one reason for /melody was the complaints about high level song fizzles, esp concerning those with the AA's to supposedly lower that rate. I would assume Sony is building a database  regarding that. 
<br />

<br />
As /melody is working right now , it is completely bugged. The few times i have used it , it made nothing but problems. Zoning with /melody for me either grays out my songs until i zone again.. or it start repeating the same song over and over again until i /melody to stop it. It does strange things when you are interrupted ... pretty useless feature. 
<br />

<br />
I agree it will help people who have bard bots, but who really cares about that. A bot'd bard is not going to sing a good twist as situations change, will be unable to mezz multiple adds ... etc.
<br />

<br />
I am by no means a bard veteran,  but the love for a manual twister is still there. Anyone can tell when your using hotkeys or /melody.   <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /></span></td>
