The big problem with this is that it is in fact, dead wrong.  As bards, we have been tought to be aware of our surroundings and question everything that is happening around us.  Other classes weren't so fortunate.
<br />

<br />
-How many times did someone in your group ask for mana song while it was already playing?
<br />

<br />
-How many times did someone ask the shaman for haste while you were already playing 130 percent haste + epic/sword proc, and if you happen to say something their answer is the horrible, too common misconception &quot;I thought they stacked!&quot;.
<br />

<br />
People don't know crap about bards.  Most bards know crap about bards too, only a few good ones actually do their homework.  
<br />

<br />
So about melody, non-bards will either not even know it exists, or will think it's something all bards use.  There's not gonna be any middle ground of people noticing who's using melody and who's not, they'll still be too busy wondering if mana song is playing.
<br />

<br />
'Stuce</span></td>
