				<td colspan="2"><span>I usually don't respond to posts like this, but somehow, someway, I just couldn't resist.
<br />

<br />
If one simple command change has ruined the bard class, then by god it must not have been much to begin with.
<br />

<br />
I have played other classes to level 50, 60 and 65 when each was the max level attainable.  Did I scream when they raised the level cap?  No.
<br />

<br />
I have played when riding a boat to get from Freeport to Butcherblock was the only way to go, and you often times took your life into your own hands doing so.  Did I scream when PoK took that need away?  No, I was relieved to not have to wait forever for a buggy ride, especially if I had just happened to miss the last boat.
<br />

<br />
I have played when you HAD to stare at a spellbook until level 30 to med.  Did I scream when they took that away?  No, I was greatful I didn't have to go through it anymore on alts.
<br />

<br />
I have played my current alt, a lvl 58 bard, for about 6-8 months, on and off.  Almost all of that time was without /melody.  And, while I learned much from both these forums and an outstanding bard in my guild, I felt almost anti-social, just due to a lack of being able to type 300wpm so I could twist and talk.  Even during downtime.
<br />

<br />
Is the implementation buggy?  When has anything from Sony not been?
<br />

<br />
Is it the death dirge for the bard class?  I don't see any rule making people use or not use it.  Personally, I use both, based on situation.  And most of the bards I know, many of whom have been playing since release, either use it situationally, or don't use it at all.  It hasn't changed a thing for them.  And they don't seem to resent the command being implemented.
<br />

<br />
This game has changed thousands of times since release, and will more than likely change a time or 2 more before the servers finally take one last donwtime.  And each time, every player has had to adjust.
<br />

<br />
As much as this comment pisses folks off, deal with it.  Everyone else has, and for just as long a time.
<br />
